<paragraph id="176C36D5FFD9FFF10392FEDFF330FDA9" blockId="14.[151,1437,152,1619]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF10392FEDFF194FED4" bold="true" box="[151,227,333,359]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFD9FFF103E8FEDEF0D7FED5" authorityName="Dusmet y Alonso" authorityYear="1921" box="[237,416,332,358]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF103E8FEDEF0D7FED5" box="[237,416,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Stelis hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was resurrected from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFD9FFF10058FEDEF5ACFED4" authority="(Lepeletier, 1841)" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[861,1243,332,359]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulata">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF10058FEDEF570FED5" box="[861,1031,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Stelis annulata</emphasis>
(Lepeletier, 1841)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="73424B24FFD9FFF1060FFEDEF0D0FE38" author="Schwarz, M. &amp; Gusenleitner, F." pageId="14" pageNumber="215" pagination="1311 - 1321" refId="ref22885" refString="Schwarz, M. &amp; Gusenleitner, F. (2010) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Stelis - Arten Spaniens (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Megachilinae). Linzer biologischer Beitrage, 42, 1311 - 1321." type="journal article" year="2010">Schwarz and Gusenleitner (2010)</bibRefCitation>
who citied multiple differences. However, as only the 
<typeStatus id="C8688877FFD9FFF1070EFEE2F51AFE39" box="[1035,1133,368,394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">holotype</typeStatus>
was known it was difficult to judge potential variation within this species, and whether it might fall within the variation seen in 
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFD9FFF1063BFE07F185FE61" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier" baseAuthorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulata">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF1063BFE07F185FE61" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">S. annulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of newly caught male material approximately 
<quantity id="D02B9B30FFD9FFF100A1FE2AF28DFE61" box="[932,1018,440,467]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" unit="km" value="250.0">250 km</quantity>
from the 
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF10769FE2AF589FE61" box="[1132,1278,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">locus typicus</emphasis>
shows that 
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFD9FFF10682FE2BF044FE45" authorityName="Dusmet y Alonso" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF10682FE2BF044FE45" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">S. hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFD9FFF10147FE4FF3B4FE45" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[578,707,476,503]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulata">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFD9FFF10147FE4FF3B4FE45" box="[578,707,476,503]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">S. annulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, supporting the position of Schwarz and Gusenleitner. The male is described here for the first time.
</paragraph>
